Petrol scarcity is biting harder in Gombe State, where black marketers and fuel attendants have continued to rip off motorists and other consumers. The Guardian gathered, yesterday, that the agony of motorists, especially commercial vehicle drivers, increased by the day, as they are always on long queues, even at ‘closed’ filling stations, hoping to get the product. According to our findings, some stations that have the product hoard it during the day for sale between midnight and 03:00 am. 